title: For Sale/Trade:  Finn-Capture Mosin Nagant
postcontent: Up for grabs is a 1939 Tula Mosin Nagant 91/30, with a Finnish capture stamp showing that it was captured some time during the Continuation War (if by the Finns), or WWII (if captured by the Germans and shipped to the Finns.  I bought this rifle a bit over a year ago, and have yet to take it out and shoot it.  Bore was fouled when I received it from being recently fired, but I cleaned out most of the fouling and you can see nice, distinct rifling.  Numbers either don't match or are force-matched, and parts are from a variety of manufacturers.  If I recall, the trigger is a Remington.  Bluing is almost completely gone on exposed metal, but looks almost new everywhere that the metal was covered by the stock/handguard.  I've tested the rifle with dummy rounds, and it feeds nice and functions very smoothly.  The trigger pull is nicer than on most Mosins, too.  The stock is really nice and worn, and shows a lot of gouges/nicks/dings/etc, but looks and feels great.  There is a crack in the stock near the tang, but I decided not to repair it, as I don't think it hurts anything.  Regarding the metal, although most of the exposed bluing is gone, there is virtually no rust at all, and several areas have a light, good looking patina.  I only saw one small spot of pitting, and it's a tiny, shallow spot about halfway up the barrel (under the wood).  Also, the bolt handle was blued at some point, which may mean that the gun is actually a German capture.  Either way, it saw combat, has the scars to prove it, and was most likely picked up on the battle field, put back together with parts and hand, and sent right back to the front (based on the non-matching numbers).Sale is F2F, and I require a bill of sale to be signed.  I also need a quick peak at your GA state ID or CCW.  I'll also show docs proving that the rifle is mine to sell.  I also have ammo I can sell for the rifle, if you need it. More pictures on request.
